<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <%- include('partials/head') %>
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/axios/dist/axios.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/gsap/3.9.1/gsap.min.js"></script>

    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f9fafb;
            color: #1f2937;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
        }

        .main-content {
            width: 90%;
            padding-left: 8rem;
            padding-right: 8rem;
            padding-top: 5rem;
            padding-bottom: 5rem;
            background-color: #ffffff;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        .title-section {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
        }

        .title-section h1 {
            font-size: 2.4rem;
            color: #2563eb;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .title-section p {
            color: #555;
            max-width: 700px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
        }

        section {
            margin-top: 2rem;
        }

        section h2 {
            font-size: 1.8rem;
            color: #333;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            border-left: 4px solid #2563eb;
            padding-left: 8px;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            cursor: pointer; /* Makes it clear that the header is clickable */
        }

        section h2 i {
            margin-right: 8px;
            color: #6f42c1;
        }

        section .faq-answer {
            font-size: 1rem;
            line-height: 1.8;
            color: #444;
            text-align: justify;
            display: none; /* Hide answers by default */
        }

        /* Sidebar styles */
        .sidebar {
            width: 25%;
            background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #007bff, #6f42c1);
            color: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            position: sticky;
            top: 0;
            height: 100vh;
            overflow-y: auto; /* Add vertical scrollbar */
        }

        .sidebar ul {
            list-style: none;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .sidebar ul li {
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .sidebar ul li a {
            color: #fff;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-size: 1rem;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            padding: 8px;
            transition: color 0.2s;
        }

        .sidebar ul li a:hover {
            color: #e0e0e0;
        }

        .sidebar ul li a i {
            margin-right: 8px;
        }

        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .main-content {
                width: 100%;
                padding: 1rem;
            }

            .sidebar {
                display: none;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <div id="progress-bar"></div>
    <%- include('partials/navbar') %>

    <div style="display: flex;">
        <aside class="sidebar">
            <ul>
                <li><a href="#faq1"><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> What is Scruter?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#faq2"><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> How do I create an account?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#faq3"><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> How do I post an ad?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#faq4"><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> What payment methods are accepted?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#faq5"><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> How can I contact support?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#faq6"><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> How do I reset my password?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#faq7"><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> How can I delete my account?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#faq8"><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> What should I do if I encounter a problem?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#faq9"><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> Can I edit my ad after posting it?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#faq10"><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> How do I report a user or an ad?</a></li>
            </ul>
        </aside>

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <main class="main-content">
            <div class="title-section">
                <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
                <p>Find answers to the most common questions about using Scruter.</p>
            </div>

            <section id="faq1">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> What is Scruter?</h2>
                <p class="faq-answer">Scruter is a local classifieds platform where users can buy, sell, and exchange services within their community.</p>
            </section>

            <section id="faq2">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> How do I create an account?</h2>
                <p class="faq-answer">To create an account, click on the "Sign Up" button and fill out the registration form with your details.</p>
            </section>

            <section id="faq3">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> How do I post an ad?</h2>
                <p class="faq-answer">Once you are logged in, navigate to the "Post Ad" section, fill in the necessary information, and submit your ad.</p>
            </section>

            <section id="faq4">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> What payment methods are accepted?</h2>
                <p class="faq-answer">Scruter accepts various payment methods, including credit/debit cards and online payment services.</p>
            </section>

            <section id="faq5">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> How can I contact support?</h2>
                <p class="faq-answer">You can reach out to our support team via the "Contact Us" section on our website or email us at support@scruter.com.</p>
            </section>

            <section id="faq6">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> How do I reset my password?</h2>
                <p class="faq-answer">If you forget your password, click on the "Forgot Password?" link on the login page and follow the instructions to reset it.</p>
            </section>

            <section id="faq7">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> How can I delete my account?</h2>
                <p class="faq-answer">To delete your account, please contact our support team, and they will assist you with the process.</p>
            </section>

            <section id="faq8">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> What should I do if I encounter a problem?</h2>
                <p class="faq-answer">If you encounter any issues, please refer to the "Help Center" or contact support for assistance.</p>
            </section>

            <section id="faq9">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> Can I edit my ad after posting it?</h2>
                <p class="faq-answer">Yes, you can edit your ad by going to your account settings and selecting the ad you wish to modify.</p>
            </section>

            <section id="faq10">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> How do I report a user or an ad?</h2>
                <p class="faq-answer">You can report a user or ad by clicking the "Report" button located next to the ad or user profile.</p>
            </section>
        </main>
    </div>

    <script>
        // Scroll Progress Bar
        window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
            const scrollTop = window.scrollY;
            const docHeight = document.body.scrollHeight - window.innerHeight;
            const scrollPercent = (scrollTop / docHeight) * 100;
            document.getElementById('progress-bar').style.width = scrollPercent + '%';
        });

        // Expand/Collapse FAQ Answers
        const questions = document.querySelectorAll('section h2');
        questions.forEach(question => {
            question.addEventListener('click', () => {
                const answer = question.nextElementSibling;
                const isVisible = answer.style.display === 'block';
                answer.style.display = isVisible ? 'none' : 'block'; // Toggle visibility
            });
        });
    </script>
</body>
<%- include('partials/footer') %>
</html>
